        <LEXMeaning Id="000102001001000" IsBiblicalTerm="Y" EntryCode="74.22" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Able, Capable</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-03-23 09:57:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to not being able to do or experience something</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>incapable</Gloss>
                <Gloss>not being able</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:04501500100018} οἱ δυνατοί refers to capability with respect to faith and τῶν ἀδυνάτων refers, conversely, to those who are incapable with respect to faith. In some languages, therefore, it may be possible to use a similar biblical phrase, weak in the faith.|In many languages the appropriate equivalent of {S:04401400800008} would be but in Lystra there was a man who was crippled.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
