        <LEXMeaning Id="000102001002000" IsBiblicalTerm="Y" EntryCode="71.3" Indent="0">
          <LEXDomains>
            <LEXDomain>Mode</LEXDomain>
          </LEXDomains>
          <LEXSubDomains>
            <LEXSubDomain>Possible, Impossible</LEXSubDomain>
          </LEXSubDomains>
          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-03-23 09:57:06" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>pertaining to being impossible, presumably because of a lack of power to alter or control circumstances</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>impossible</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>In {S:05800600400002} the use of ἀδύνατον seems to be an instance of hyperbole in view of the warnings against apostasy (see {S:05800501100000-05800601200000}). Therefore, one may translate ἀδύνατον in {S:05800600400002} as ‘it is extremely difficult to.’ TEV introduces a rhetorical question to express strong doubt, “for how can those who abandon their faith be brought back to repent again?”</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
